body:
@janl while porting this PR to `main` it looks like inadvertently swapped the `?OTP_RELEASE` macro name with `?OTP_VERSION`. 

Notice in https://github.com/apache/couchdb/pull/3422#discussion_r593935304 it's `?OTP_RELEASE` but the final PR had `?OTP_VERSION` in https://github.com/apache/couchdb/pull/3422/files#diff-f95fbb47ac3f26db5ba353a42e63b998a104084db1aa3c0d149179163fa777fbR237

To double check: https://erlang.org/doc/reference_manual/macros.html#predefined-macros

Right, if you _don't_ set the security object yourself, it is implicitly;

```
{
  "members" : { "roles" : [ "_admin" ] },
   "admins" : { "roles" : [ "_admin" ] }
}
```

which means only admins can read/write/etc.

If you _change_ it to `{}`, you are opening it up to everyone.
